# Python Rules
## Always apply

### Imports
- Sort imports using isort standards
- Group imports into: standard library, third-party, local
- Remove unused imports
- Use absolute imports for project modules

### Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 guidelines
- Maximum line length: 100 characters
- Use type hints for function parameters and return values
- Use docstrings for classes and functions (Google style)
- Use f-strings for string formatting
- Use snake_case for functions and variables
- Use PascalCase for classes

### ML-specific
- Use torch.device for device management
- Initialize random seeds for reproducibility
- Use context managers for torch.no_grad() when appropriate
- Log model parameters and hyperparameters
- Use proper error handling for CUDA operations

### Testing
- Place test files in appropriate directories
- Use descriptive test names
- Include assertions for expected outputs
- Mock external dependencies

### Documentation
- Update docstrings when modifying functions
- Include examples in docstrings where appropriate
- Document any assumptions in complex algorithms
- Add inline comments for complex logic

### Performance
- Use vectorized operations where possible
- Profile memory usage for large models
- Implement proper cleanup for GPU memory
- Use appropriate batch sizes

### Security
- No hardcoded credentials
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Validate input data
- Sanitize file paths
